 "cells": [

   "id": "1314f82b-ceb2-4b98-a442-ea4b5fe8aca6",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Introduction to multi-task deep neural network for single-cell multi-omics data (scMultiNet)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a16cedbc-eae2-4f4c-a611-863289e391b0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "In this introductory tutorial, we present the different tasks of a **scMultiNet** workflow\n",
    "\n",
    "- 1. Loading the multi-omics data\n",
    "- 2. Training the scMultiNet model\n",
    "- 3. Integration into the common latent space\n",
    "- 4. Prediction from modality 1 to modality 2\n",
    "- 5. Denoising for multi-modality data"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9f63913d-447c-41cb-a7e5-a12a0fadccd1",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "import the necessary packages"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "fe99ac05-6d95-4522-8cb3-3b3b4d335215",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "%matplotlib inline\n",
    "import os\n",
    "import torch\n",
    "import random\n",
    "import warnings\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import scanpy as sc\n",
    "import anndata as ad\n",
    "\n",
    "from MultiNet.trainer import Trainer\n",
    "from MultiNet.dataloader import SingleCellMultiOmicsData\n",
    "from MultiNet.multinet import MultiNet\n",
    "from MultiNet.preprocess import setup_seed\n",
    "from MultiNet.eval_tools import clustering_metric\n",
    "from MultiNet.configs import *\n",
    "warnings.filterwarnings(\"ignore\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "096086a6-3113-4551-a4ce-00e88d72d517",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**seed**: Sets the random seed for reproducibility.  \n",
    "**device**: Specifies the hardware device used for computation (e.g., cpu, cuda)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "4e484724-a06f-4ada-9154-1ab0d322ff72",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "setup_seed(42)\n",
    "device = torch.device(\"cuda\" if torch.cuda.is_available() else \"cpu\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "19f4752c-2ac2-42c9-8a31-ca1e65d94aec",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step1: Loading data"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "8175dbdc-cfde-456a-956f-ea22d371efa8",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "loading the **BMNC** dataset.  \n",
    "- **configs**: Configuration information of scMultiNet (hyperparameters, network settings, data preprocessing, etc.)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "f2dcf5de-40c4-42bc-9505-5b3f010d68ed",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "configs = citeseq_config\n",
    "configs['use_indicator'] = False  # Set it to True when performing denoising tasks.\n",
    "Dataname = 'BMNC'\n",
    "data_path = None"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "d8623ccb-9344-4856-9a0e-93cabc59771a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Chosen offset: 0.13\n",
      "==> Successfully preprocessed 2000 genes and 30672 cells.\n",
      "==> Successfully preprocessed 25 proteins/peaks and 30672 cells.\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "data = SingleCellMultiOmicsData(Dataname, configs, data_path)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b3785292-9a8a-4305-9863-459247614ef3",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step2: train your scMultiNet model\n",
    "You can either train the scMultiNet model yourself or load the weights we provide."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "88654020-89d1-43b6-a7d7-b47f63e31151",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "multinet = MultiNet(data.n_vars_list, configs)\n",
    "multinet = multinet.to(device)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "494f104e-6f45-4d38-ad1c-74cb88a173e5",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Pretrain...\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Epoch 100/100 g_Loss:0.665433 d_Loss:0.002773 : 100%|█████████████| 100/100 [03:20<00:00,  2.01s/it]\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "==> Pretrain Done\n",
      "Train...\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Epoch 200/200 g_Loss:0.440291 d_Loss:0.002786 : 100%|█████████████| 200/200 [11:33<00:00,  3.47s/it]"
     ]
    },
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "==> Train Done\n",
      "==> saving checkpoint 'BMNC.pth.tar'\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "train = True\n",
    "save = True\n",
    "weight_path = 'BMNC.pth.tar'\n",
    "if train:\n",
    "    trainer = Trainer(data, multinet, device)\n",
    "    trainer.train(configs)\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    multinet.load_weight(weight_path)  \n",
    "\n",
    "# if save:\n",
    "    multinet.save_weight(weight_path)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "5f36efa9-60b2-4b7d-a7a3-f510915981e2",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step3: Task of Multi-Modality Integration\n",
    "**Integrate** multi-omic data and use **UMAP** to visualize the clustering results"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "7a27a1f8-a031-4ea9-82fe-8cda176d36c5",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from sklearn.cluster import KMeans\n",
    "figsize = (3, 3)\n",
    "n_neighbors=20\n",
    "min_dist=0.5"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "954124f2-c61a-484e-a4f4-7e4d12e17824",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "27\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "x = data.get_one_epoch_data(device)\n",
    "Y =  data.get_celltypes()\n",
    "class_num = len(np.unique(Y))\n",
    "kmeans = KMeans(n_init=20, n_clusters=class_num, random_state=42)\n",
    "print(class_num)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "id": "e86a98ca-f617-4938-908c-76311184e349",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "com = multinet.ae_network.get_common_latent_representation(x)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "id": "2e57203d-d5b3-4f94-94ae-b0b057ea20e0",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 216x216 with 0 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "adata = ad.AnnData(X=com)\n",
    "adata.obs['cell_types'] = Y.astype(str)\n",
    "sc.pp.neighbors(adata, n_neighbors=n_neighbors, use_rep=\"X\")\n",
    "sc.tl.umap(adata, min_dist=min_dist)\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=figsize)\n",
    "sc.pl.umap(adata, color=['cell_types'], title=\"scMultiNet\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "id": "14e7be5a-1533-47e8-8043-e822a27014da",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "NMI: 0.8411, ARI: 0.8757\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "y_pred = kmeans.fit_predict(adata.X)\n",
    "NMI, ARI = clustering_metric(Y, y_pred)\n",
    "print('NMI: {:.4f}, ARI: {:.4f}'.format(NMI, ARI))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e0f76e3c-56b2-4d15-a302-9f4fe164883c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step4: Task of Cross-Modality Prediction  \n",
    "Demo: Prediction from **RNA** to **ADT**  \n",
    "In this demo, we used the complete BMNC dataset for both testing and training, so the results may differ from those reported in the paper."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "id": "4bb368ff-7436-4795-9991-568d6ee3eddb",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "raw_adt = x[1].cpu().detach().numpy()\n",
    "corss_adt = multinet.ae_network.get_cross_modality_RNA2ADT(x[0])\n",
    "# raw_rna = x[0].cpu().detach().numpy\n",
    "# cross_rna multinet.ae_network.get_cross_modality_ADT2RNA(x[1])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "id": "a578c866-a75a-4f58-ba2d-f990cbfd2d48",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "ncols = 2\n",
    "nrows = 1\n",
    "figsize = 4\n",
    "wspace = 0.5\n",
    "\n",
    "adata_raw = ad.AnnData(X=raw_adt)\n",
    "adata_cross = ad.AnnData(X=corss_adt)\n",
    "adata_raw.obs['cell_types'] = Y.astype(str)\n",
    "adata_cross.obs['cell_types'] = Y.astype(str)\n",
    "sc.pp.neighbors(adata_raw, n_neighbors=n_neighbors, use_rep=\"X\")\n",
    "sc.pp.neighbors(adata_cross, n_neighbors=n_neighbors, use_rep=\"X\")\n",
    "sc.tl.umap(adata_raw, min_dist=min_dist)\n",
    "sc.tl.umap(adata_cross, min_dist=min_dist)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "id": "7e46c68d-bbe6-4051-bf14-988a657d33d3",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 720x288 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, axs = plt.subplots(\n",
    "    nrows=nrows,\n",
    "    ncols=ncols,\n",
    "    figsize=(ncols * figsize + figsize * wspace * (ncols - 1), nrows * figsize),\n",
    ")\n",
    "sc.pl.umap(adata_raw, color=['cell_types'], title=\"ADT Raw\", ax=axs[0], show=False)\n",
    "axs[0].get_legend().remove() \n",
    "sc.pl.umap(adata_cross, color=['cell_types'], title=\"RNA to ADT\", ax=axs[1])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "id": "bf652498-1c73-489c-aa5b-1a2fab9f4a5c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Raw  : NMI: 0.7516, ARI: 0.5333\n",
      "Cross: NMI: 0.6738, ARI: 0.5118\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "y_pred = kmeans.fit_predict(adata_raw.X)\n",
    "NMI1, ARI1 = clustering_metric(Y, y_pred)\n",
    "y_pred = kmeans.fit_predict(adata_cross.X)\n",
    "NMI2, ARI2 = clustering_metric(Y, y_pred)\n",
    "print('Raw  : NMI: {:.4f}, ARI: {:.4f}'.format(NMI1, ARI1))\n",
    "print('Cross: NMI: {:.4f}, ARI: {:.4f}'.format(NMI2, ARI2))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d72649fa-3763-47dc-b483-2b53b4e6253a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step5: Task of Multi-Modality Data Denoisiong\n",
    "Perform this task only when training with indicator matrices and test it using data with artificial dropout."
   ]
  },
